  "prompt": "In IIT Bombay medical studies are there or not?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, the **Indian Institute of Technology Bombay (IIT Bombay)** does **not offer traditional medical degree programs** (such as MBBS). IIT Bombay is primarily renowned for its engineering, technology, and science programs, including undergraduate, postgraduate, and doctoral studies in various specialized fields.\n\nHowever, IIT Bombay does engage in interdisciplinary research and offers programs that intersect with the biomedical field, such as:\n\n- **Biomedical Engineering**: This program combines engineering principles with biological sciences to develop technologies and devices for healthcare.\n- **Biotechnology**: Focused on applying biological systems and organisms to develop products and technologies beneficial to healthcare and other industries.\n- **Collaborative Research Initiatives**: IIT Bombay collaborates with medical institutions and hospitals for research in areas like healthcare technology, medical devices, and computational biology.\n\nIf you're interested in pursuing a career in medicine, you might consider institutions specifically dedicated to medical education, such as:\n\n- **All India Institute of Medical Sciences (AIIMS)**\n- **Jawaharlal Institute of Postgraduate Medical Education and Research (JIPMER)**\n- **National Institutes of Health (various across India)**\n- **Private and state-run medical colleges**\n\nFor interdisciplinary studies that bridge engineering and medicine, IIT Bombay could be a valuable place, especially if you're interested in areas like medical technology, biomedical research, or healthcare innovation. It's advisable to check the latest information on IIT Bombay's [official website](https://www.iitb.ac.in/) or contact their admissions office for the most up-to-date details regarding available programs and courses.",
